      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Yes. Many couples update their agreement after they’ve been married for a while in order to keep up with changing assets and circumstances. This commonly occurs when a spouse enters into a business partnership with another person and wants to protect the assets of the business from the other spouse (or the spouse from the risk involved in the business). Other significant life events could also prompt a couple to revisit their prenup. As long as you both agree, you can update your prenup as often as you want. You can even cancel it, as long as both parties agree."
    }
