    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Can I include my pets in a prenup?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Yes. If you owned the pet before marriage, you can use your prenup to designate who the pet will go to if you split up. This is because pets are technically property under Virginia law, and subject to the normal rules surrounding the division of assets. However, for a pet acquired after marriage, the court will usually award the pet to the person who was most involved in caring for it."
